## 📅 12-Month Study Timeline

### Months 1–2 — Tech Foundations
- [ ] Networking basics — TCP/IP, DNS, firewalls, VPNs
- [ ] Windows & Linux command line
- [ ] Security mindset — CIA triad, encryption, threats

**Resources:**
- TryHackMe.com — Pre-Security learning path (free)
- Professor Messer — YouTube (free)
- Google IT Support Certificate — Coursera

---

### Months 3–4 — First Certification
- [ ] Study for CompTIA Security+
- [ ] Complete Jason Dion course on Udemy (~$15 on sale)
- [ ] Pass the exam ✅

**Resources:**
- Udemy — Jason Dion (Security+)
- Professor Messer practice tests
- CompTIA CertMaster Labs

---

### Months 5–7 — Cloud Foundations
- [ ] Create free AWS account and explore the console
- [ ] Earn AWS Cloud Practitioner cert
- [ ] Start AWS Solutions Architect Associate

**Resources:**
- Stephane Maarek on Udemy (best AWS courses)
- AWS free tier account — hands-on practice
- A Cloud Guru

---

### Months 8–10 — Cloud Security Specialty
- [ ] Pursue AWS Security Specialty certification
- [ ] Learn IAM, CloudTrail, GuardDuty, Security Hub
- [ ] Build hands-on labs in your AWS free account

**Resources:**
- AWS Security Specialty course (Udemy)
- AWS official documentation
- CloudGoat (vulnerable-by-design AWS labs)

---

### Months 11–12 — Job Ready Push
- [ ] Build portfolio — document home lab projects on GitHub
- [ ] Optimize LinkedIn with certifications and projects
- [ ] Apply to entry-level roles:
  - Junior Cloud Security Engineer
  - Cloud Security Analyst
  - Associate SOC Analyst (stepping stone)
- [ ] Network with cloud security professionals on LinkedIn

---

## 🔧 Key Skills to Build

